|rowspan=3| {{flag|Kentucky}}&lt;ref&gt;[https://revenue.ky.gov/Individual/Individual-Income-Tax/Pages/default.aspx Individual Income Tax], Kentucky Department of Revenue.&lt;/ref&gt;{{efn|Most counties, some municipalities and some school districts in this state tax income, most using a flat rate but some using regressive rates.&lt;ref&gt;[https://www.kentoncounty.org/232/Rates Rates], Kenton County.&lt;/ref&gt; Where a county, municipal or school district tax exists, the combined rate ranges from 0.45 to 4.25% depending on the location.&lt;ref name=mercer&gt;[https://mercercounty.ky.gov/fiscal-court/Pages/Tax-Administrator.aspx Tax Administrator], Mercer County.&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[https://cumberlandcounty.ky.gov/docs/Pages/Documents.aspx Important Documents], Cumberland County.&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref name=KLC&gt;[https://www.klc.org/userfiles/files/OccLiclTaxRatesCities2020.pdf City Occupational Tax Rates], Kentucky League of Cities, 21 October 2019.&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref name=KYSD&gt;[https://education.ky.gov/districts/SEEK/Pages/Taxes.aspx Taxes], Kentucky Department of Education, 16 March 2020.&lt;/ref&gt;}} ||rowspan=3| 5% || [[List of counties in Kentucky|most counties]]&lt;ref name=mercer/&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[https://montgomerycounty.ky.gov/Dept/Pages/Occupational-Tax-Forms.aspx Occupational Tax Forms], Montgomery County.&lt;/ref&gt; || 0.45 to 2%
